A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
To commend and honor Dr. Paul Dean Coreil on the occasion of his retirement as
Chancellor of Louisiana State University of Alexandria and to recognize his many
accomplishments in higher education, public service, youth development, and the
Louisiana Cooperative Extension Service.
WHEREAS, Dr. Paul Dean Coreil has devoted more than forty-three years of
distinguished service to the LSU System, including thirteen years on the campus of
Louisiana State University of Alexandria and eight years as Chancellor of LSUA, and his
career reflects an extraordinary commitment to the people and communities of Louisiana;
and
WHEREAS, Dr. Coreil returned to LSUA in 2019 with a bold vision for growth,
access, innovation, and public service, and under his leadership the university experienced
one of the most transformative periods in its history; and
WHEREAS, during his tenure as chancellor, LSUA achieved record enrollment
growth, surpassing an ambitious goal of increasing enrollment by fifty percent within five
years in only three years, and growing to more than eight thousand students, a one hundred
forty-five percent increase during his tenure; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Coreil's leadership helped establish LSUA as the fastest-growing
university in Louisiana for four consecutive years and elevated the university to the fifth
largest university in the state, while continuing to expand educational opportunity for
students across Louisiana and beyond; and
WHEREAS, under his leadership, LSUA reached another all-time enrollment record
of seven thousand seven hundred twenty-eight students in the Spring 2026 semester, further
demonstrating the sustained institutional momentum achieved during his administration; and
